records.addlTxt: Absolute sobriety, defendant is not to possess or consume any alcohol.  Defendant to have no contact with the Hampton Inn in the Town of Brookfield listed in the Criminal Complaint.

2:05 PM Defendant Danalee J Gray in court, in custody.  District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin by Julian Marrufo.  The Court goes over the procedural history of the case. Court advises of right to an attorney.  The State gives its bail recommendation.  Defendant states she was in the hospital on August 8, 2022 when she missed Court and was under the impression her last Court date was set for 4:00 pm.  Court conducts colloquy with the defendant in regards to any hospital stays since the last Court date.  Court quashes warrant.  The Court will reinstate the signature bond so it does not go to judgment and in its place set cash bail in the amount of $1,000.
Hearing scheduled for October 12, 2022 at 09:30 am.
